because if it's happened once, maybe it'll happen again. and I was devastated losing the friend last year, and I'll also be devastated to lose this friend my brain has latched on to recently. what if my brain is actually right??

in the last few months, one has slipped through. I've been beginning to think that one friend has decided I'm too much, too weird, maybe there was a misunderstanding I didn't realize and they didn't bring up but have been harboring against me, maybe I'm just too difficult, etc

and I certainly don't want to be that friend that needs constant validation that my friends are my friends because they sincerely like me, and not because they pity me or whatever. (but gods fighting brainworms is HARD.)

which is fine! except my OCD really latches on to obsessive thoughts, especially trying to see patterns everywhere. and I've been fighting it, so hard. it can't possibly be right. it is statistically ridiculous that all my friends secretly think poorly of me

I've been trying to accept that some friendships end, especially in a pandemic where everyone's bubbles had to get smaller. so that this was a sort of cutting a dead branch for the overall health of the tree.

so I distanced myself (easy to do in a pandemic). it was such terrible allegations I figured it was too late to change things. defending myself from falsehoods wouldn't change their mind if they had been thinking of me like that, for that long.

last May (2021) I found out that someone I thought was my friend actually thought very poorly of me, in some really terrible ways. I was shocked they thought I would do things I would never do! they really must have thought the worst of me for a really long time.
